The reason the previous code didn't work is likely because of the helper function `add_error_comment_to_PN_cell` in your original code.

**The Problem:**
Your original `add_error_comment_to_PN_cell` function searches the **entire sheet** for every instance of a Part Number and adds a comment to all of them. So, even if my logic correctly identified that *only* the second block had an error, calling your helper function would accidentally force the error comment onto the first block (and every other block) too.

**The Solution:**
We must modify the specific cell **directly** without searching the whole sheet again.

Here is the corrected, complete code block to replace the validation section in `main_code`.

### Step 1: Add this updated function inside your script

(You can place this inside `class App` or just above `main_code`. If inside the class, add `self.` where appropriate).

